
* Special Issue: Multitude 11 on Social Struggles

=Summary=

Michel Bauwens:

Yann Moulier-Boutang, in an article on the crisis of the left, summarizes the 3 great social movements of the last century

    - The movement for social solidarity, which started in 1848 but lost prestige due to the failures of the Soviet system and the management of neoliberal decline by the social democrats
    - The movement for national liberation but which failed the solve the social problem in the South
    - the post-1968 fights for freedom and recognition, such as feminism, etc ..

